Business Brief -- Hitachi Metals Ltd.:
   Profit and Sales Estimates
   For Fiscal Year Are Cut
The company said auto and auto-related industry
performance didn't meet expectations, while demand was
sluggish in both the computer market and building
construction. Price competition also had a significant impact
on domestic and overseas performance, Hitachi Metals said.
   Sales are seen falling 4% to 445 billion yen from 463.72
billion yen, lower than the previous forecast of 470 billion
yen. Net income is expected to plunge 53% to 7.5 billion yen
from 16.07 billion yen. The May estimate put net at 16
billion yen.